EventItemTitle:
By The Speaker (Council Member Quinn):
Pursuant to Rule 11.20(c) of the Council and Section 197-d(b)(3) of the New York City Charter, the Council hereby resolves that the action of the City Planning Commission on Uniform Land Use Procedure Applications no. C 070305 ZSM, a special permit to allow the development of a 37 space accessory parking garage within the cellar 405-427 W. 53rd Street, shall be subject to Council review.

INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York City Charter in relation to changing the compensation of members of the city council.
EventItemMatterName: Changing the compensation of members of the city council.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to amend Article 11 of the New York State Environmental Conservation Law to add Quaker parrots to the list of “protected birds,” which will oblige the City to take all possible steps to humanely relocate Quaker parrots that have nested on city-owned properties that are slated for demolition or removal or where other projects require removal of the birds.
EventItemMatterName: Amend Article 11 of the NYS Environmental Conservation Law to add Quaker parrots to the list of “protected birds".

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to unattended vehicles.
EventItemMatterName: Unattended vehicles.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to making available to all Parent Associations, Parent Teacher Associations and Community Education Councils the equipment necessary to enable such entities to webcast their meetings.
EventItemMatterName: Making available to all Parent Associations, Parent Teacher Associations and Community Education Councils the equipment necessary to enable such entities to webcast their meetings.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter in relation to the powers of the fire commissioner.
EventItemMatterName: Powers of the fire commissioner.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to collecting and reporting data related to youth aging out of foster care.
EventItemMatterName: Collecting and reporting data related to youth aging out of foster care.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the federal government to recognize legally married same-sex couples in the 2010 census, and to begin counting lesbian, gay, bisexual and transgender individuals in other federal surveys.
EventItemMatterName: Federal government to recognize legally married same-sex couples in the 2010 census, and to begin counting lesbian, gay, bisexual and transgender individuals in other federal surveys.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to requiring the New York city department of education to provide the metropolitan transportation authority with certain student enrollment information.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the NYC dept of education to provide the metropolitan transportation authority with certain student enrollment information.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Rights
EventItemTitle: Resolution condemning the New York Post for its racist depiction of President Barack Obama in a political cartoon.
EventItemMatterName: Condemning the New York Post for its racist depiction of President Barack Obama in a political cartoon.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York City Charter, in relation to requiring the City Record to be published online and available to the public at no charge.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the City Record to be published online and available to the public at no charge.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs

EventItemMatterName: Creation of a Street Vendor Advisory Board.

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to allowing members of the New York City Police Department to remain in service until age sixty-five.
EventItemMatterName: Allowing members of the New York City Police Department to remain in service until age sixty-five.
